    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Tyler Freeman** (72.83) and **Will Smith** (71.28) anchor the LawDog lineup as our strongest plays. Both hitters benefit from favorable matchups against pitchers with high xERAs\u2014Sasaki (5.52) and Lorenzen (4.16)\u2014coupled with significant park factor boosts. **Tyler Freeman** is particularly well-positioned, as he maximizes the 14% park advantage and the 19% SP skill edge while batting in a protected #4 spot. Meanwhile, **Will Smith** continues to be a high-floor producer; his combination of hitting in the heart of the order and a strong 0.378 xwOBA makes him an essential piece against a middling right-handed arm. We are also capitalizing on **Jonathan Aranda** (66.50) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (66.01), both of whom offer elite value today; **Jonathan Aranda** specifically gains a massive boost from a 12% dynamic platoon advantage and favorable wind conditions that should help him leverage his 0.382 xwOBA against M. Keller.\n\nThe most difficult decision on our bench was **Matt Chapman** (52.74), who just barely missed the cut. While his underlying metrics are solid, he is being sidelined in favor of the higher efficiency outputs from **Bryson Stott** and **Jonathan Aranda**, both of whom are projected to capitalize more effectively on today\u2019s specific pitcher matchups. We are closely monitoring the risk profile of **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez**, as both face Crochet; despite the park boost, Crochet\u2019s elite skill profile creates a 19% handicap that drags their scores down, making them low-end starts that we are keeping on a short leash to preserve our game caps. If the wind shifts or lineup configurations change, we may pivot to **Masyn Winn** or **Gavin Sheets** if their matchups against Burrows or Urena present a clearer path to production than the current bottom-third of our rotation.",
